2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20rejected%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20last-ditch%20effort%20to%20block%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fny-judge-sets-trumps-hush-money-sentencing-january-10-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20hush-money%20sentencing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20now%20remains%20set%20for%209%3A30%20a.m.%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court's%20decision%20means%20Trump%20must%20attend%20or%20face%20a%20potential%20bench%20warrant%20for%20his%20arrest%20just%2010%20days%20before%20Inauguration%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20conservative%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20Clarence%20Thomas%2C%20Samuel%20A.%20Alito%2C%20Neil%20M.%20Gorsuch%2C%20and%20Brett%20M.%20Kavanaugh%20%E2%80%94%20had%20sided%20with%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20conservatives%20on%20the%20panel%20%E2%80%94%20Chief%20Justice%20John%20G.%20Roberts%20and%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%20%E2%80%94%20broke%20ranks%20and%20supported%20Manhattan%20prosecutors.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20one-page%20order%2C%20the%20five-judge%20majority%20gave%20two%20reasons%20for%20rejecting%20Trump's%20attempt%20to%20halt%20the%20sentencing.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20the%20alleged%20evidentiary%20violations%20at%20President-Elect%20Trump's%20state-court%20trial%20can%20be%20addressed%20in%20the%20ordinary%20course%20on%20appeal%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20post-sentencing%2C%20they%20wrote.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BSecond%2C%20the%20burden%20that%20sentencing%20will%20impose%20on%20the%20President-Elect's%20responsibilities%20is%20relatively%20insubstantial%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote%2C%20given%20that%20Trump%20faces%20a%20no-punishment%20sentence%20and%20can%20attend%20the%20hearing%20virtually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20last%20week%20asked%20that%20he%20be%20allowed%20to%20attend%20by%20video%2C%20a%20request%20approved%20by%20his%20trial%20judge%2C%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Juan%20Merchan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20did%20not%20oppose%20Trump%20attending%20virtually%20and%20said%20Thursday%20that%20his%20office%20will%20not%20seek%20jail%2C%20fines%2C%20or%20probation%20at%20what%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20very%20brief%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25483247-24a666-order%2F%3Fembed%3D1%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20New%20York%20sentencing%20guidelines%2C%20Trump%20had%20faced%20as%20little%20as%20zero%20jail%20time%20and%20as%20much%20as%20four%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20his%20May%2030%20conviction%20on%2034%20felony%20counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20Manhattan%20jury%20found%20he%20altered%20Trump%20Organization%20invoices%20and%20other%20records%20throughout%20his%20first%20year%20in%20office%20in%20order%20to%20retroactively%20hide%20a%20%24130%2C000%20hush%20money%20payment%20that%20silenced%20porn%20actress%20Stormy%20Daniels%20eleven%20days%20before%20the%202016%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20legal%20scholar%20stated%2C%20unequivocally%2C%20that%20this%20is%20a%20case%20that%20should%20never%20have%20been%20brought%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20a%20Truth%20Social%20post%20Thursday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20case%20against%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20nothing%20other%20than%20Weaponization%20of%20our%20Justice%20System%20against%20a%20Political%20Opponent.%20It's%20called%20Lawfare%2C%20and%20nothing%20like%20this%20has%20ever%20happened%20in%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%2C%20and%20it%20should%20never%20be%20allowed%20to%20happen%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3ESpeaking%20minutes%20after%20the%20SCOTUS%20order%20from%20Mar-a-Lago%2C%20Trump%20promised%20to%20appeal%20his%20conviction%20and%20repeated%20that%20the%20prosecution%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Battack%20on%20a%20political%20opponent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20much%20more%20important%20than%20tomorrow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20his%20planned%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20had%20fought%20hard%20to%20avoid%20sentencing%2C%20despite%20facing%20little%20inconvenience%20or%20penalty%20beyond%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-nj-liquor-licenses-at-risk-again-if-sentenced-friday-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotential%20issues%20with%20his%20New%20Jersey%20liquor%20licenses.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20week%2C%20his%20lawyers%20had%20argued%20in%20four%20courthouses%20%E2%80%94%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20Albany%2C%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%20%E2%80%94%20that%20any%20invocation%20of%20presidential%20immunity%20automatically%20entitles%20Trump%20to%20a%20stay%20pending%20appeal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffighting-hush-money-case-trump-says-presidents-elect-are-immune-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20before%20he%20is%20sworn%20in%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20opposition%20filings%2C%20Manhattan%20prosecutors%20scoffed%20at%20the%20idea%20that%20%26quot%3Bpresident-elect%20immunity%26quot%3B%20is%20even%20a%20thing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-january-6-election-ruling-decision-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court's%20landmark%20July%201%20opinion%3C%2Fa%3E%20granted%20presidents%20broad%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%2C%20but%20made%20no%20mention%20of%20immunity%20prior%20to%20swearing%20in%2C%20lawyers%20for%20Bragg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDefendant's%20novel%20invocation%20of%20President-elect%20immunity%20does%20not%2